{
  "stem": "4361.9",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then, he said, I don't think you should because you know, you-- I, I want a house maker.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And now, I was a good girl.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I wish I would have been my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I began to do what was expected of me, you know, being the wife of a fairly successful attorney, socially and so forth.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Nonetheless, I did get very much involved in Jewish affairs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Starting with the synagogue, I was the president of this or that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Eventually, I became a very important person in Hadassah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And then came Ralph in '6-- I got married in 1957, and Ralph came in 1963, at which point there was no way that I would go back to school.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And this is when I became involved in Jewish affairs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I kept being involved in Jewish affairs until 1976, which was around Ralph's bar mitzvah-- my son's bar mitzvah-- which was one of the happiest days in my life when I saw him being bar mitzvahed.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That Rabbi Nedicz, who was the rabbi at the time at the Park Avenue Synagogue, said something which I wanted him to say, which I asked him to say, and he said it before the full congregation.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said, you see, Ralph, the fact that you are now bar mitzvahed means that those bad people, the Nazis, did not win.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You are here, and you are a Jew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That made it a very meaningful and happy day in my life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was in 1976.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then, I said to my husband, Herman, like it or not, I am going back to college.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was not a good girl because he said, why?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You are so busy with this, and you are so busy with that.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
